Class Fingerprint

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.nih.ncats.molwitch.fingerprint.Fingerprint

    Class that represents a "fingerprint" for a single Chemical generated by a Fingerprinter.

    • Method Detail

      • fromBinaryString

        public static Fingerprint fromBinaryString(String fp)
        Create a new Fingerprint instance from the given binary String. The leftmost position is the most significant bit so 10010100 will have a fingerprint with 1's on at 2, 4, 7.
        Parameters:
        fp - the fingerprint as a binary string; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new Fingerprint object
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if fp is null

      • and

        public Fingerprint and(Fingerprint other)
        Perform a logical AND operation between this Fingerprint and the other given fingerprint, The result is then returned as a new Fingerprint. This operation does no modify either input fingerprints.
        Parameters:
        other - the other Fingerprint to AND; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a new Fingerprint containing the result.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null.

      • compatible

        public boolean compatible(Fingerprint other)
        Is this fingerprint "compatible" with the other given fingerprint. Compatibility is defined as having both fingerprints have 1s set where this fingerprint has a 1 set.
        Parameters:
        other - the other fingerprint to compare to; can not be null.
        Returns:
        true if these fingerprints are compatible; false otherwise.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null.

      • populationCount

        public int populationCount()
        Get the Population count of this fingerprint which is the number of bits set to true in this fingerprint.
        Returns:
        the number of bits set to true in this fingerprint.

      • toBitSet

        public BitSet toBitSet()
        Convert this fingerprint to a BitSet. Please note, the returned BitSet may have different lengths and sizes depending on what bits are set in the fingerprint.
        Returns:
        the BitSet; will never be null.

      • hammingDistance

        public int hammingDistance(Fingerprint other)
        Get the hamming distance between this Fingerprint and the given other Fingerprint. This can be thought of as the minimum number of bits to flip to convert from one Fingerprint into the other.
        Parameters:
        other - the other Fingerprint to find the hamming distance between; can not be null.
        Returns:
        the hamming distance as an int.

      • tanimotoSimilarity

        public double tanimotoSimilarity(Fingerprint other)
        Compute the Tanimoto Similarity (also known as Jaccard Index or Jaccard Similarity Coefficient) which measures how similar this Fingerprint is compared to the other given Fingerprint.
        Parameters:
        other - the other Fingerprint to compare to; can not be null.
        Returns:
        a double between 0 and 1 where two identical fingerprints will return 1.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null.

      • tanimotoSimilarityShortCircuit

        public OptionalDouble tanimotoSimilarityShortCircuit(Fingerprint other)
        Compute the Tanimoto Similarity (also known as Jaccard Index or Jaccard Similarity Coefficient) which measures how similar this Fingerprint is compared to the other given Fingerprint except the method will short circuit and return OptionalDouble.empty() if this fingerprint logical and'ed to the other fingerprint don't have the same value. This will make calculations that are probably not similar enough to end early.
        Parameters:
        other - the other Fingerprint to compare to; can not be null.
        Returns:
        an OptionalDouble between 0 and 1 of empty if the fingerprints are too dissimilar. Two identical fingerprints will return 1.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null.

      • jaccardDistanceTo

        public double jaccardDistanceTo(Fingerprint other)
        Compute the Jaccard Distance to the other given Fingerprint.
        Parameters:
        other - the other Fingerprint to compare to; can not be null.
        Returns:
        The distance which is defined as 1- tanimotoSimilarity(other).
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if other is null.
